    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-chorizo-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the pasta, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-chorizo-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chorizo has crisped, add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min further until starting to soften</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the tomatoes are soft, add the <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and cook, covered, for 1-2 min or until the spinach has wilted</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-chorizo-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-chorizo-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the spinach has wilted, add <strong>half</strong> your<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>goats' cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up until fully combined</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-chorizo-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta is cooked, add it to the pan with the sauce</p><p>Stir everything together and cook for 1-2 min further or until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta \u2013 this is your <strong>goats' cheese, chorizo & spinach pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if the sauce is looking a little thick!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-chorizo-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crumble the <strong>remaining goats' cheese</strong> into rough bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-chorizo-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>goats' cheese, chorizo & spinach pasta </strong>with the <strong>remaining goats' cheese</strong> sprinkled over the top</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped basil</strong> and <strong>remaining chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
